<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Chronicles_of_Narnia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=41" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Bruner, Kurt &amp; Ware, Jim. <i>Finding God in the Land of Narnia</i>. Tyndale House Publishers, 2005.</li>
<li>Bustard, Ned. <i>The Chronicles of Narnia Comprehension Guide</i>. Veritas Press, 2004.</li>
<li>Duriez, Colin. <i>A Field Guide to Narnia</i>. InterVarsity Press, 2004.</li>
<li>Downing, David. <i>Into the Wardrobe: C. S. Lewis and the Narnia Chronicles</i>. Jossey-Bass, 2005.</li>
<li>Hein, Rolland. <i>Christian Mythmakers: C. S. Lewis, Madeleine L'Engle, J.R.R. Tolkien, George MacDonald, G.K. Chesterton, &amp; Others Second Edition</i>. Cornerstone Press Chicago, 2002. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/094089548X" class="internal">ISBN 094089548X</a></li>
<li>Jacobs, Alan. <i>The Narnian: The Life and Imagination of C. S. Lewis</i>. HarperSanFrancisco, 2005.</li>
<li>McIntosh, Kenneth. <i>Following Aslan: A Book of Devotions for Children</i>. Anamchara Books, 2006.</li>
<li>Wagner, Richard. <i>C. S. Lewis &amp; Narnia For Dummies</i>. For Dummies, 2005.</li>
<li><i>A Guide for Using The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe in the Classroom</i>. Teacher Created Resources, 2000.</li>
<li><i>The Lion, Witch &amp; Wardrobe Study Guide</i>. Progeny Press, 1993.</li>
<li><i>The Magician's Nephew Study Guide</i>. Progeny Press, 1997.</li>
<li><i>Prince Caspian Study Guide</i>. Progeny Press, 2003.</li>
</ul>
